After rekindling their relationship in 2020. The Closer singer and the mother of three of his children exchanged vows on the rooftop of Resorts World in Las Vegas on Sunday night in front of close friends and family, according to TMZ. Videos and pictures posted by the couple on Instagram show their lavish reception, which was filled with more than 10,000 red roses. Ne-Yo, real name Shaffer Smith, also reportedly sang some of his hits and they danced to Ed Sheeran's Thinking Out Loud.